                            <li>
                                <div class="content">
                                    <span>Language -</span> English
                                </div>
                                <div class="info">
                                     
                                    <div class="tooltip-text">English is widely spoken in tourist areas.</div>
                                </div>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Agra is one of India’s most famous historical cities and a must-visit destination for travelers exploring North India. Located in the state of Uttar Pradesh, Agra is globally renowned for the Taj Mahal, a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the Seven Wonders of the World. The city reflects the rich legacy of the Mughal Empire, with magnificent monuments, beautiful gardens, and vibrant local markets.

                        Apart from the Taj Mahal, Agra is home to other iconic attractions such as Agra Fort, Itmad-ud-Daulah (Baby Taj), Mehtab Bagh, and the nearby UNESCO site Fatehpur Sikri. The city is also famous for its marble inlay handicrafts, leather goods, and traditional sweets like Petha. Because of its historical significance and cultural charm, Agra forms an essential part of the popular Golden Triangle Tour (Delhi – Agra – Jaipur).

                        Agra offers visitors a unique blend of history, architecture, Mughal culture, and local craftsmanship, making it one of the most visited tourist destinations in India.</p>
                         
